<br>
And so we are expecting doctors to be perfect now?  It's one thing to sue if it was negligence by the doctors allowing the girl not to be saved.  But incorrectly estimating the extent of the injuries is not necessarily negligence.  Do you honestly believe doctors are infallible?  If a hospital cannot locate the cause of a disease quickly enough, should they be sued?<br>
<br>
Of course not.  They are doing whatever is possible to help people, to the best of their abilities.<br>
<br>
Should a football player get sued because they were trusted to make the game-winning catch, and missed it?  No.<br>
<br>
This is almost the same situation, except it's alot more emotional because someone died.  But just because its a sensitive situation doesn't mean common sense should be thrown out the window.<br>
<br>
The doctors performed to the best of their ability.  Sueing them for not being perfect is ridiculous.  It is this kind of crap that is causing medical walkouts in this country.  The last thing we need are physicians afraid to help people out of fear of what may happen if they fail. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205399">My Gear Sucks less now!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eudamanslayer>EudaManslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 1074<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/14/03 6:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3168.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: That's it!</span><hr size=1> yah what ever, people watch Hockey for the fights. Its like &quot;Boxing ON ICE.&quot; Pucks shatter the plexyglass and shoot up and through the stands alot more then they used to. Its a fact. If some dude for the Yankys blew a line drive and shatterd somebodys nose thoth, who covers the damage? The ball club? The bat manufactuer? <br>
