<br>
That's why doctors carry malpractice insurance.<br>
<br>
And cases like this are why malpractice insurance is so expensive.  For some specialties, it can easily run over $100K per year.  It's gotten so bad that some doctors in Pennsylvania stopped performing certain types of surgery last year, to pressure the governor to enact legislation addressing the problem.<br>
<br>
And expensive malpractice insurance is one of the reasons (not the only reason, but one of the reasons) that health insurance premiums and health care costs generally are so high.  <br>
<br>
So who pays the settlement in this case?  In the long run, you do.  <br>
<br>
Disclaimers on the ticket?  Please.  You can have language that is crystal clear, you can make the guy sign the damn disclaimer and initial every word to make sure he read it, you can even paint &quot;you might die sitting here from a puck&quot; on the back of every seat.  If a judge doesn't think the outcome is &quot;fair&quot;, in his own view of fairness, he won't give a damn how clear the warnings were.  Welcome to the U.S. legal system today, someone else is always to blame.  As someone else said earlier, there's no such thing as an accident any more.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eudamanslayer>EudaManslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 1076<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/14/03 7:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3168.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: That's it!</span><hr size=1> How many people have died in Hockey games? Comepare it to the number of people who have died to being hit by COMETS, subtract the numer of people who have sponteniously cumbust due to the ammout of McDonalds frenchfrys they had, and count the number of BAD Godzilla movies, and you then subtract the number of people who actualy think Bush is NOT a moron. That remaining number is the base line for ...something. I forget what. But the point is, Alstate does life inshurance. And only people who are realy stuck up, or realy rich sue. And if anybody ever trys to sue me I swear to god I'll kill them. Then sue them back. Then kill mysef for sueing them. And then sue myself for killing myself. and the....<br>
